'''Synthetic mycoides''' refers to an [[artificial life]] form created by [[Craig Venter]] at the [[J Craig Venter Institute]] in May 2010.<ref>{{cite journal|first1=Daniel G. |last1=Gibson|first2=John I. |last2=Glass|first3= Carole |last3=Lartigue|first4= Vladimir N. |last4=Noskov|first5= Ray-Yuan |last5=Chuang|first6= Mikkel A. |last6=Algire|title=Creation of a Bacterial Cell Controlled by a Chemically Synthesized Genome|journal=Science|volume=329|issue=5987|pages=52-56|date=2 July 2010|doi=10.1126/science.1190719}}</ref> A synthetic [[genome]] was transferred into an empty cell to form the [[bacterium]], which was capable of self replication and functioned solely from the transferred chromosomes.<ref>BBC news, ''"Artificial life" breakthrough announced by scientists'', Victoria Gill. Retrieved 20 May 2010. [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/science_and_environment/10132762.stm]</ref>

